  "commentary": "With SPX at 7082.82 sitting between the massive +12.7B gamma wall at 7100 and the 7050 support at +6.3B, dealers are positioned to fade any move higher into 7100 where they'll aggressively sell the rally. The PIN regime confirms dealers are long gamma and will provide stabilizing flow, with the recent wall break event likely triggering some mechanical rebalancing flows. Watch 7100 as the key resistance level where dealer selling pressure intensifies, while 7050 provides the nearest meaningful support with substantial positive gamma.\n\nBottom line: expect the market to get pinned between 7050-7100 with selling pressure on any push toward 7100.",
